race.comment: BROWN NOSE DAY GAL (6) was a very impressive winner last start at Oakbank, and the subsequent form around her is stacking right up. Gets a kilo off with the slight rise in grade and is well placed to make it two on the bounce. MAGIC PRINCESS (7) chased in vain behind BNDG two back, then improved sharply to get the bob at Oakbank last time. Draws well and gets her chance to turn the tables. ELLIOTTO (3) has mixed his form so far this campaign but has peaks that measure up. Cherry-ripe now and draws well for Opperman, who knows him well. Holds genuine appeal if he's presented on song. JOVIALE (9) never looked likely last time when always well back in the field. Was too bad to be true and is capable of much better. Willing to give another chance, though he will need some luck from the wide gate.
